    "B14 found that under the legacy detector, E7a / E7b / E7c produce byte-identical statistics — the detector cannot distinguish bare-alef from hamza-bearing-alef substitutions.",
    "Under the hamza-preserving parallel detector, channels that differ across the 3 sub-classes (n_channels_fixed_hamza > 0) represent the architectural fix: those channels can now tell ع↔ا apart from ع↔أ apart from ع↔آ.",
    "Production-grade B14b would (i) re-train channels B/G on the hamza-preserving alphabet, (ii) re-run exp46/exp50 with the new detector to see if any of the 16 audited no-E7 detections gain hamza-sensitivity, (iii) verify that the headline H1_STRUCTURAL_ARABIC_BLINDNESS / H2_QURAN_SPECIFIC_IMMUNITY verdict from B16 doesn't shift under the new detector. Estimated additional effort: 1-2 weeks engineering + re-runs."
